<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="255" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1938,2035]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="255" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1938,1963]" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male imago: 1) general coloration: thorax and abdomen dark brown, sterna light brown (
<figureCitation box="[1270,1393,1938,1963]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1891,1913]" captionTargetBox="[180,1396,381,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,337,1869]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male imagos, general view. A–B) Simothraulopsis sinuosus sp. nov.: A, lateral view; B, abdominal color pattern (dorsal view). C–D) Simothraulopsis gracilianus sp. nov.: C, lateral view; D, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460072/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Fig. 2A–B</figureCitation>
); 2) hind wing with costal projection forming a right angle, located approximately 1/2 distance from base to apex of wing (
<figureCitation box="[223,357,2010,2035]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[179,1400,229,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imagos, wings. A–C) Simothraulopsis gracilianus sp. nov. A, forewing; B, hind wing; C, enlarged hind wing. D–F) Simothraulopsis sinuosus sp. nov.: D, forewing; E, hind wing; F, enlarged hind wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460074/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Figs. 3B–C</figureCitation>
); 3) abdominal terga II–VII with medio-basal translucent yellow angles (
<figureCitation box="[1188,1324,2010,2035]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1891,1913]" captionTargetBox="[180,1396,381,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,337,1869]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male imagos, general view. A–B) Simothraulopsis sinuosus sp. nov.: A, lateral view; B, abdominal color pattern (dorsal view). C–D) Simothraulopsis gracilianus sp. nov.: C, lateral view; D, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460072/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Figs. 2A–B</figureCitation>
); 4) penis projection spine-like, sinuous, median size (approximately half of the total length of penis lobes), slightly laterally directed (
<figureCitation box="[256,390,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1905,1927]" captionTargetBox="[179,1373,240,1833]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male imagos, genitalia, ventral view. A–B) Simothraulopsis sinuosus sp. nov. A, general aspect; B, penis, detail (ventral view). C–D) Simothraulopsis gracilianus sp. nov.: C, general view; D, penis, detail." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460076/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="255">Figs. 4A–B</figureCitation>
); 5) penis lobes fused on basal half, with a shallow concavity in the junction of the lobes (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1891,1913]" captionTargetBox="[180,1396,381,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,337,1869]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male imagos, general view. A–B) Simothraulopsis sinuosus sp. nov.: A, lateral view; B, abdominal color pattern (dorsal view). C–D) Simothraulopsis gracilianus sp. nov.: C, lateral view; D, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460072/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="255">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
