<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1328]" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,270,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Head.</emphasis>
Dorsal region dark brown, with black marks; ventral region brown. Upper portion of compound eyes reddish brown, lower portion black (
<figureCitation box="[560,651,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1891,1913]" captionTargetBox="[180,1396,381,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,337,1869]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male imagos, general view. A–B) Simothraulopsis sinuosus sp. nov.: A, lateral view; B, abdominal color pattern (dorsal view). C–D) Simothraulopsis gracilianus sp. nov.: C, lateral view; D, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460072/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Scape and pedicel of antenna brown, flagellum whitish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1328]" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,223,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotum dark brown, margins black; with a submedial black stripe. Mesonotum dark brown; longitudinal medial, anterolateral scutal, lateroparapsidal and medioparapsidal sutures light brown; posterior scutal protuberance, scuto-scutellar impression and scutellum black. Pleura brown washed with dark brown; membranous area yellowish. Metanotum dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[619,712,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1891,1913]" captionTargetBox="[180,1396,381,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,337,1869]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male imagos, general view. A–B) Simothraulopsis sinuosus sp. nov.: A, lateral view; B, abdominal color pattern (dorsal view). C–D) Simothraulopsis gracilianus sp. nov.: C, lateral view; D, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460072/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Sterna light brown, sutures darker. Wings membrane hyaline. Forewing with longitudinal veins whitish yellow and cross veins translucent; costal brace and base of veins C, Sc and anal section dark brown; fork of vein MP slightly symmetric (
<figureCitation box="[935,1028,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[179,1400,229,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imagos, wings. A–C) Simothraulopsis gracilianus sp. nov. A, forewing; B, hind wing; C, enlarged hind wing. D–F) Simothraulopsis sinuosus sp. nov.: D, forewing; E, hind wing; F, enlarged hind wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460074/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Hind wing with costal projection developed, forming a right angle, located approximately 1/2 distance from base to apex of wing (
<figureCitation box="[1287,1423,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[179,1400,229,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imagos, wings. A–C) Simothraulopsis gracilianus sp. nov. A, forewing; B, hind wing; C, enlarged hind wing. D–F) Simothraulopsis sinuosus sp. nov.: D, forewing; E, hind wing; F, enlarged hind wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460074/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Figs. 3B–C</figureCitation>
); longitudinal and cross veins yellowish brown, except basal part of costal and subcostal vein; costal region translucent, posterior part of lower portion of hind wing tinged with brown (
<figureCitation box="[1051,1154,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[179,1400,229,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male imagos, wings. A–C) Simothraulopsis gracilianus sp. nov. A, forewing; B, hind wing; C, enlarged hind wing. D–F) Simothraulopsis sinuosus sp. nov.: D, forewing; E, hind wing; F, enlarged hind wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460074/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Figs. 3C</figureCitation>
). Coxae and trochanters yellowish, washed with gray. Leg. I: femur yellowish brown with a blackish line on posterior margin; tibia with a blackish basal band, remainder whitish; tarsi whitish. Legs II and III similar to leg I.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1328]" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,620,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Terga orangish brown, anterior margins lighter (
<figureCitation box="[893,984,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1891,1913]" captionTargetBox="[180,1396,381,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,337,1869]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male imagos, general view. A–B) Simothraulopsis sinuosus sp. nov.: A, lateral view; B, abdominal color pattern (dorsal view). C–D) Simothraulopsis gracilianus sp. nov.: C, lateral view; D, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460072/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Terga I, VIII– IX completely brown; terga II–VII with anterior region and lateral margin yellowish; tergum X yellowish with a black spot medially (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1891,1913]" captionTargetBox="[180,1396,381,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,337,1869]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male imagos, general view. A–B) Simothraulopsis sinuosus sp. nov.: A, lateral view; B, abdominal color pattern (dorsal view). C–D) Simothraulopsis gracilianus sp. nov.: C, lateral view; D, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460072/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Sterna light brown. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[557,660,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1905,1927]" captionTargetBox="[179,1373,240,1833]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male imagos, genitalia, ventral view. A–B) Simothraulopsis sinuosus sp. nov. A, general aspect; B, penis, detail (ventral view). C–D) Simothraulopsis gracilianus sp. nov.: C, general view; D, penis, detail." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460076/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Figs. 4A</figureCitation>
). Styliger plate yellowish brown. Forceps segment I darkish brown, segments II and III lighter. Segment II 0.13 length of segment I, 1.4 length of segment III. Penis lobes whitish, fused on basal 1/3; almost pointed apically, separated by a distance either greater than width of one penis lobe, with a spine-like, sinuous, median size (approximately half of the total length of penis lobes) projection, slightly laterally directed; inner margins of lobes divergent, with a medial shallow concavity between them (
<figureCitation box="[1331,1423,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1905,1927]" captionTargetBox="[179,1373,240,1833]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male imagos, genitalia, ventral view. A–B) Simothraulopsis sinuosus sp. nov. A, general aspect; B, penis, detail (ventral view). C–D) Simothraulopsis gracilianus sp. nov.: C, general view; D, penis, detail." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460076/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="258">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Caudal filaments whitish, except basal region brown and apical margin of each segment black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
